    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/hemolysis-literature-synthesis",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis model literature synthesis — aggregated prior-study concordance",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior published studies examining CFD hemolysis model performance across rotary blood pump geometries. Draws on at least eleven independent experimental campaigns spanning 2008–2022, covering a range of shear-stress exposure histories and erythrocyte damage power-law exponents. The synthesis demonstrates consistent model concordance within ±18% across pump families and supports the applicability of the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law formulation to the FDA generic pump geometry. This node represents the consolidated evidentiary basis for model form credibility and was assembled by the V&V team as a standing reference artifact."
    },
