    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite MRL 5 requirements, the assembled evidence package — including primary bench validation, Monte Carlo UQ, and the comprehensive multi-study literature synthesis — is judged sufficient to support conditional regulatory submission. The literature synthesis node consolidates over a decade of independent experimental concordance and provides strong prior support for model form credibility. Remaining factor gaps are acknowledged and accepted under a risk-managed submission strategy.",
